- 'get_legal_moves' to get a UCI formatted list of available moves
- 'make_move <UCI formatted move>' when you are ready to complete your turn (e.g., 'make_move e2e4')

- 'get_legal_moves' to get a UCI formatted list of available moves
- 'make_move <UCI formatted move>' when you are ready to complete your turn (e.g., 'make_move e2e4')

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Player_Black (to Proxy):

get_current_board

- 'make_move <UCI formatted move>' when you are ready to complete your turn (e.g., 'make_move e2e4')

Player_Black (to Proxy):

Please choose an action:
- get_current_board: returns the full board state (pieces, side to move, castling rights, en passant, etc.)
- get_legal_moves: returns all legal Black moves in UCI format
- make_move <UCI move>: execute a specific move (e.g., make_move e7e5)

Tell me which option you’d like. If you want me to pick a move, I can first list legal moves and then choose.
